      <prefercite id="ref1">
         <head>Cite As</head>
         <p>Glenn Lowell Jepsen Archives, Vertebrate Paleontology, Yale Peabody Museum</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="ref2">
         <head>Biographical Sketch</head>
         <p>Glenn Lowell Jepsen (b. 1903, d. 1974), the first to hold the appointment of Sinclair Professor of Vertebrate Paleontology at Princeton University, served the university, and the Princeton Geological Museum in particular, for some 49 years.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref4">
         <head>Description of the Material</head>
         <p>The archives of Glen Lowell Jepsen include field notes, coresspondence, and manuscript materials all relating to the Princeton collection.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
